Manchester City striker, Gabriel Jesus has been included in the UEFA Champions League team of this week. UEFA released the Champions League team in a post on their official website on Thursday. Jesus was included in the team after his impressive performance in his side’s 4-1 victory against Dinamo Zagreb on Wednesday. The Brazilian international scored a hat-trick against Dinamo. Jesus made the list, alongside Paris Saint-Germian’s Kylian Mbappe and Napoli’s Arkadiusz Milik. UEFA Champions League team after match-6 is found below: Goalkeeper: Alisson Becker (Liverpool) Defender: Timothy Castagne (Atalanta), Felipe (Atlético), Robin Gosens (Atalanta), Alex Grimaldo (Benfica) Midfielder: Pizzi (Benfica), João Félix (Atlético), Phil Foden (Man. City) Forward: Gabriel Jesus (Man. City), Arkadiusz Milik (Napoli), Kylian Mbappé (Paris) Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.